# Search Input Standards

- When implementing any search feature in frontend pages/components, use `@front-end/src/components/common/SearchInput.tsx`.
- Do not create ad-hoc search UI using raw `Input` + icon wrappers when `SearchInput` can satisfy the use case.
- Prefer `SearchInput` props (for example `value`, `onChange`, `onDebouncedChange`, `debounceDelay`, and placeholder text) instead of custom debounce/search wiring duplicated in page components.
- Keep search behavior reusable and consistent across pages by standardizing on `SearchInput`.

## Exceptions

- Use a custom search control only when the feature has requirements not supported by `SearchInput` (for example: specialized tokenized search UX).
- If an exception is required, add a short code comment explaining why `SearchInput` is not being used.
